<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Portfolio • Your Name</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Moderator/Manager portfolio and resume." />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    :root{
      --bg:#2b2b2f;          /* page background */
      --panel:#37373c;       /* card background */
      --ink:#f4f4f5;         /* text */
      --muted:#c8c8ce;       /* secondary text */
      --accent:#6ee7b7;      /* green */
      --accent-2:#60a5fa;    /* blue */
      --pill:#1f1f22;        /* badge bg */
      --shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
      --radius: 24px;
    }
    *{box-sizing:border-box}
    html,body{margin:0;height:100%}
    body{font-family:Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,Segoe UI,Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;background:radial-gradient(1200px 600px at 10% -10%, #3b3b40 0, #2b2b2f 50%), var(--bg);color:var(--ink);line-height:1.6}
    a{color:inherit}
    .wrap{max-width:1100px;margin:40px auto;padding:0 20px}
    .shell{background:var(--panel);border-radius:48px;padding:40px 40px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
    @media (max-width: 800px){.shell{padding:28px;border-radius:28px}}

    /* header */
    .header{display:grid;grid-template-columns:260px 1fr;gap:32px;align-items:center}
    @media (max-width: 900px){.header{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:18px;text-align:center}}
    .pfp{width:120px;height:120px;border-radius:50%;object-fit:cover;border:4px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.35)}
    .role-pill{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;background:var(--pill);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);padding:8px 14px;border-radius:999px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.2px}
    .name{font-size:46px;line-height:1.05;margin:12px 0 8px;font-weight:800}
    .sub{color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 8px}
    .cta{display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:14px;justify-content:flex-start}
    @media (max-width:900px){.cta{justify-content:center}}
    .btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;padding:12px 16px;border-radius:14px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);background:#2a2a2e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600}
    .btn:hover{transform:translateY(-1px);transition:.15s ease}
    .btn.primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--accent),var(--accent-2));color:#111;font-weight:800}

    /* layout */
    .grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.2fr .8fr;gap:26px;margin-top:28px}
    @media (max-width: 1000px){.grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}}
    .card{background:#323238;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:24px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
    .card h3{margin:0 0 12px;font-size:20px}
    .muted{color:var(--muted)}

    /* lists */
    .kpis{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:12px}
    @media (max-width:700px){.kpis{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}
    .kpi{background:#2a2a2f;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);border-radius:18px;padding:16px;text-align:center}
    .kpi b{font-size:22px;display:block}

    .skills{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px}
    .pill{background:#2a2a2f;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);padding:8px 12px;border-radius:999px;font-weight:600}

    .timeline{display:grid;gap:16px}
    .item{display:grid;grid-template-columns:120px 1fr;gap:16px}
    .item .when{color:var(--muted)}
    @media (max-width:600px){.item{grid-template-columns:1fr}.item .when{order:2}}

    .projects{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:16px}
    @media (max-width:900px){.projects{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
    .proj{padding:18px;border-radius:18px;background:#2a2a2f;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06)}
    .proj h4{margin:6px 0 8px}
    .proj p{margin:0}

    .footer{margin-top:24px;text-align:center;color:var(--muted);font-size:14px}

    /* optional mc skin image on left for desktop */
    .skin{max-width:220px;filter:drop-shadow(0 16px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.45))}
    @media (max-width:900px){.skin{display:none}}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="shell">
      <header class="header">
        <div style="display:flex;gap:18px;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
          <!-- Replace src with your avatar URL -->
          <img class="pfp" src="https://placehold.co/240x240/png" alt="Profile" />
          <img class="skin" src="https://placehold.co/220x320/png?text=MC+Skin" alt="Minecraft skin" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="role-pill">Professional Moderator / Manager</span>
          <h1 class="name">Your Name</h1>
          <p class="sub">I keep communities fair, friendly, and thriving. 2+ years of experience across large Minecraft networks.</p>
          <div class="cta">
            <a class="btn primary" href="#contact">Contact Me</a>
            <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/youruser" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
            <a class="btn" href="https://wahaboo.carrd.co" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Portfolio</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>About me</h3>
          <p>Hey! I’m <b>Your Name</b>. I’ve been a Moderator and Manager in the Minecraft community for over two years, working with large servers and fast‑moving teams. I focus on fair rule enforcement, conflict resolution, mentor‑style leadership, and building an inclusive player experience. I’m proactive, communicative, and always looking for ways to improve operations.</p>

          <div class="kpis" style="margin-top:16px">
            <div class="kpi"><b>2+ yrs</b><span class="muted">Moderation</span></div>
            <div class="kpi"><b>60k+</b><span class="muted">Community Size</span></div>
            <div class="kpi"><b>6+</b><span class="muted">Servers Supported</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Skills</h3>
          <div class="skills">
            <span class="pill">Moderation & Policy</span>
            <span class="pill">Team Leadership</span>
            <span class="pill">Ticket & Escalations</span>
            <span class="pill">Conflict Resolution</span>
            <span class="pill">Community Events</span>
            <span class="pill">Staff Training</span>
            <span class="pill">Discord & In‑game Tools</span>
            <span class="pill">Analytics & Reporting</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="grid" style="margin-top:18px">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Experience</h3>
          <div class="timeline">
            <div class="item">
              <div class="when">2024–2025</div>
              <div>
                <b>FreshSMP</b> — Moderator (60k+ members)
                <p class="muted">Handled high‑volume tickets, coordinated with senior staff for fair and consistent enforcement, and contributed to community safety initiatives.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="item">
              <div class="when">2023–2024</div>
              <div>
                <b>Rewindbox</b> — Moderator (5.7k+)
                <p class="muted">Monitored chats, managed reports and appeals, and helped streamline escalation guidelines.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="item">
              <div class="when">2023–2024</div>
              <div>
                <b>MineCrush</b> — Helper ➜ Moderator (5k+)
                <p class="muted">Promoted based on reliability; resolved player conflicts and improved FAQ / auto‑responses to reduce ticket load.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="item">
              <div class="when">2019–2023</div>
              <div>
                <b>TerraMC • Sellable • Voltage • CrystalChaos</b>
                <p class="muted">Various Helper/Moderator roles supporting player experience and staff coordination.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>What I bring</h3>
          <p>Calm judgment, clear communication, and a team‑first mindset. I value collaboration and shared ownership, and I’m comfortable making decisions under pressure. I’m active, responsive, and enjoy mentoring new staff to help the whole team level up.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
        <h3>Highlighted projects</h3>
        <div class="projects">
          <div class="proj">
            <small class="muted">Playbook</small>
            <h4>Moderation Handbook</h4>
            <p class="muted">A concise guide for helpers and mods covering policies, escalation ladders, evidence standards, and tone guidelines.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="proj">
            <small class="muted">Automation</small>
            <h4>Discord Workflow</h4>
            <p class="muted">Ticket presets, canned replies, and structured tags that cut average response times by ~25%.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="contact" class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
        <h3>Contact</h3>
        <p class="muted">Available for Moderator/Manager roles and collaboration.</p>
        <div class="cta">
          <!-- Replace with your links -->
          <a class="btn primary" href="mailto:you@example.com">Email</a>
          <a class="btn" href="https://discord.com/users/yourid" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Discord</a>
          <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/youruser" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
          <a class="btn" href="https://linktr.ee/youruser" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Linktree</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="footer">© <span id="y"></span> Your Name — Built with hand‑rolled HTML/CSS</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script>document.getElementById('y').textContent = new Date().getFullYear()</script>
</body>
</html>
